<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="17" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="17">
For detailed morphology see 
<bibRefCitation author="Cuccodoro, G" editor="Cuccodoro, G" journalOrPublisher="Memoirs on Entomology, International, Gainesville (Vol. 17)" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" pagination="359 - 455" refId="B4" refString="Cuccodoro, G, 2003. A revision of Megarthrus Curtis of India, Nepal and Sri Lanka (Coleoptera, Staphylinidae, Proteininae). In: Cuccodoro, G, Leschen, RAB, Eds., Systematics of Coleoptera: Papers celebrating the retirement of Ivan Loebl. Memoirs on Entomology, International, Gainesville (Vol. 17): 359 - 455" title="A revision of Megarthrus Curtis of India, Nepal and Sri Lanka (Coleoptera, Staphylinidae, Proteininae)." volumeTitle="Systematics of Coleoptera: Papers celebrating the retirement of Ivan Loebl." year="2003">Cuccodoro (2003)</bibRefCitation>
. Combined length of head, pronotum, and elytra 1.6-1.9 mm; maximal pronotal width = 0.9-1.1 mm. Body (Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 4–6" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figures 4 - 6. Megarthrus flavolimbatus Cameron: habitus, male: dorsal 4 ventral 5 and lateral 6 views. Scale bar: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1056.66553.figures4-6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/578544" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">4-6</figureCitation>
) predominantly chestnut brown, with pronotum slightly paler along lateral edges, frons slightly paler than vertex, and legs slightly paler than elytra. Anterior frontal margin slightly carinate, more convex at middle than laterally in dorsal view.
</paragraph>
<caption doi="10.3897/zookeys.1056.66553.figures4-6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/578544" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" start="Figures 4–6" startId="F2">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="17">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Figures 4-6.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cameron" authorityYear="1924" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Megarthrus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Megarthrus flavolimbatus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavolimbatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Megarthrus flavolimbatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Cameron: habitus, male: dorsal 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">4</emphasis>
ventral 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">5</emphasis>
and lateral 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">6</emphasis>
views. Scale bar: 0.5 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="17">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Male</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Protibia fairly straight and evenly expanding from base to apex; adventral side shallowly depressed transversely. Mesotrochanter with about a dozen peg-like setae arranged in two rows. Mesofemur fairly straight and slightly swollen. Mesotibia subangulate, bearing peg-like setae arranged in one row. Metatrochanter and metafemur slightly swollen; posterior margin of metatrochanter evenly arcuate; inner margin of metafemur fairly straight in ventral view, forming sharp ridge on entire length. Metatibia swollen, at middle forming conspicuous tooth-like process projecting above flattened apical portion of metatibia; metatibial peg-like setae grouped as a dense field on apical third, discontinuously with 1 peg-like seta to at most 7 peg-like setae on distal side of tooth-like process; proximal side of tooth-like process convex, with at most 1 peg-like seta. Aedeagus (Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 10–18" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figures 10 - 18. Megarthrus dentipes Bernhauer (10, 13, 16) M. flavolimbatus Cameron (11, 14, 17) M. hemipterus (Illiger) (12, 15, 18) male: aedeagus in ventral (10 - 12) and lateral (13 - 15) views female: genital segments, dorsal part (16 - 18) in ventral view. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1056.66553.figures10-18" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/578546" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">11</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 10–18" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figures 10 - 18. Megarthrus dentipes Bernhauer (10, 13, 16) M. flavolimbatus Cameron (11, 14, 17) M. hemipterus (Illiger) (12, 15, 18) male: aedeagus in ventral (10 - 12) and lateral (13 - 15) views female: genital segments, dorsal part (16 - 18) in ventral view. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1056.66553.figures10-18" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/578546" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">14</figureCitation>
) with ventral wall slightly narrowed at base and evenly narrowed to acutely angled apex in ventral view, and with ventral outline fairly straight to slightly recurved apex in lateral view.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="17">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Female</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Gonocoxal plate with lateral portions of dorsobasal margin with oblique to middle portion truncate, markedly projecting anterad. Dorsal part of genitalia (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 10–18" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figures 10 - 18. Megarthrus dentipes Bernhauer (10, 13, 16) M. flavolimbatus Cameron (11, 14, 17) M. hemipterus (Illiger) (12, 15, 18) male: aedeagus in ventral (10 - 12) and lateral (13 - 15) views female: genital segments, dorsal part (16 - 18) in ventral view. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1056.66553.figures10-18" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/578546" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">17</figureCitation>
) with evenly thick semi-circular sclerite.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
