<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="17" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Distribution and natural history.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="17">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cameron" authorityYear="1924" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Megarthrus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Megarthrus flavolimbatus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavolimbatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Megarthrus flavolimbatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the most widespread member of the genus in the Oriental Realm, with records ranging from North India (Himachal Pradesh and West Bengal) to Yunnan Province and Taiwan in China (
<bibRefCitation author="Cuccodoro, G" editor="Cuccodoro, G" journalOrPublisher="Memoirs on Entomology, International, Gainesville (Vol. 17)" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" pagination="359 - 455" refId="B4" refString="Cuccodoro, G, 2003. A revision of Megarthrus Curtis of India, Nepal and Sri Lanka (Coleoptera, Staphylinidae, Proteininae). In: Cuccodoro, G, Leschen, RAB, Eds., Systematics of Coleoptera: Papers celebrating the retirement of Ivan Loebl. Memoirs on Entomology, International, Gainesville (Vol. 17): 359 - 455" title="A revision of Megarthrus Curtis of India, Nepal and Sri Lanka (Coleoptera, Staphylinidae, Proteininae)." volumeTitle="Systematics of Coleoptera: Papers celebrating the retirement of Ivan Loebl." year="2003">Cuccodoro 2003</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Cuccodoro, G" journalOrPublisher="Studies and reports, taxonomical Series" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" pagination="25 - 92" refId="B5" refString="Cuccodoro, G, 2011. Megarthrus of Taiwan, with notes on phylogenetic relationships within the genus (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Proteininae). Studies and reports, taxonomical Series 7 (1-2): 25 - 92" title="Megarthrus of Taiwan, with notes on phylogenetic relationships within the genus (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Proteininae)." volume="7" year="2011">2011</bibRefCitation>
); here, we report it for the first time also from Fujian, Hunan, Shaanxi and Sichuan Provinces in China (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 41" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figure 41. Distribution map in China of Megarthrus dentipes Bernhauer, M. flavolimbatus Cameron, M. hemipterus (Illiger) and Megarthrus panda sp. nov. Scale bar: 300 km." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1056.66553.figure41" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/578551" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">41</figureCitation>
). It was found at elevations ranging from 250 to 3375 m a. s. l. in Taiwan (
<bibRefCitation author="Cuccodoro, G" journalOrPublisher="Studies and reports, taxonomical Series" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" pagination="25 - 92" refId="B5" refString="Cuccodoro, G, 2011. Megarthrus of Taiwan, with notes on phylogenetic relationships within the genus (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Proteininae). Studies and reports, taxonomical Series 7 (1-2): 25 - 92" title="Megarthrus of Taiwan, with notes on phylogenetic relationships within the genus (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Proteininae)." volume="7" year="2011">Cuccodoro 2011</bibRefCitation>
), and its altitudinal range appears quite wide also in mainland China (i.e., from 1000 to 1700 m a. s. l. in Fujian, from 7000 to 1200 m a. s. l. in Hunan, from 1850 to 2480 m a. s. l. in Yunnan, from 650 to 2400 m a. s. l. in Sichuan, and at 1200 m a. s. l. in Shaanxi). The species occurs in various types of forests (evergreen broadleaved, deciduous broadleaved, mixed coniferous and evergreen broadleaved, and coniferous forests) as well as in orchards, where it was collected mainly from sifted samples of moist decaying debris of vegetation (leaf litter, humus, rotting wood) with fungi, and occasionally even from chicken excrement (
<bibRefCitation author="Cuccodoro, G" journalOrPublisher="Studies and reports, taxonomical Series" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" pagination="25 - 92" refId="B5" refString="Cuccodoro, G, 2011. Megarthrus of Taiwan, with notes on phylogenetic relationships within the genus (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Proteininae). Studies and reports, taxonomical Series 7 (1-2): 25 - 92" title="Megarthrus of Taiwan, with notes on phylogenetic relationships within the genus (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Proteininae)." volume="7" year="2011">Cuccodoro 2011</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
